node.text: Everyone should have access to the performing arts. They provide an outlet for self expression, an opportunity for creative inspiration, and a shared experience to bond and build community. Now more than ever before we need to support and encourage artists and venues so we can continue the essential act of story telling and the universal language of art. I am so grateful to have the arts in my life and pledge to share them with people whenever I can. Thank you all so much for sharing my @dancingabc experience with me and helping to support all the amazing artists who make that show possible.

node.text: Nothing but smiles for me today. Huge congratulations to @kaitlynbristowe and @theartemc for a job well done and thank you all so much for taking this ride with me. Thank you @dancingabc for believing in me and shining such a bright light on dance and creativity. Thank you @jennajohnson for being the best teacher, partner and friend I could have ever asked for. Last but not least thank you @lauraperlongo for supporting and encouraging me on this journey and taking such great care of our kids in my absence. I can’t wait to come home to my real life dance partner. So much love to all of you and have a safe and joyful holidays. 😘

node.text:
It’s been a tough year. In March my wife and I had Covid. It was really scary as there was so little information available and we were terrified that our kids would get sick too. For over three weeks, my constant fatigue, headaches and difficulty breathing was awful and the stress of wondering if my symptoms would worsen was horrifying. Thank God my condition improved and our kids didn’t get sick and we were able to safely quarantine. With all the fear, uncertainty, and unrest that has followed its been a roller coaster of emotions for all of us. It’s hard to believe that despite all that, my year is ending with one of the most positive and amazing experiences of my life. I am so blessed that I have my family and that we have our health. This year has taught me so much about gratitude, focus and the unpredictability of life. It’s taught me to appreciate what I have and not take anything for granted, least of all my health. My heart goes out to all who have lost loved ones this year and I pray that a vaccine comes soon so we can all move past this together. Please remember to be kind to one another and that there is far more that unites us than divides us. 

I could not have made it through this year without my phenomenal wife, partner, and best friend @lauraperlongo. You are powerful beyond belief and I am more grateful for you every day. I love you. 

Thank you @jennajohnson for your partnership, patience and artistry. You turned this dad into a dancer and I am forever grateful. 

Huge shout out to all the amazing people who make @dancingabc possible. Dance is such a powerful art form and I’m so thrilled that this show brings the joy of dance to so many. 

And thanks to all of YOU for your support. It has been an incredible privilege performing for you these past 10 weeks. See you next Monday in the finale! #TeamBeNeevers #DWTS

node.text: As I’ve grown older I’ve realized that annual events like birthdays and anniversaries aren’t just about celebrating you or your partners special day, they are opportunities to look back and take stock of your life. Reflecting on the past four years I realize just how lucky I have been. Watching my wife create life and bring a person into the world was the single most magical experience of my life. Being around these incredible women has completely changed my understanding and appreciation for the feminine force, and I am a better man every day because of them. Thank you both for sharing your energy, compassion and creativity with me and always reminding me to have more fun. You are such bright lights and beautiful souls and I’m so lucky to have you in my life. Happy giving-birth-day @lauraperlongo, and thank you for making our birthday angel @cleojames_studio 🥰

node.text: It’s been six years since we swapped spit and you stole my heart. Thank you for being the answer to all my questions, the combination to my lock and the key to my map. I don’t know much, but I do know that everyday I get to be with you is going to be fun and new and expansive in more ways than I could ever imagine. I love you more than you will ever believe and would go on that first date with you a million times. Happy 1st date anniversary my love. #6years
